expressionParser

Class OperandNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • expressionParser.ExprNode
      • expressionParser.OperandNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IVisitable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    GenericOperation

    public abstract class OperandNode
extends ExprNode
    OperandNode class represents a leaf node in the expression tree. This node is a simple expression such as "le name NAME" or "ge value 5.0". It is used to check if a pair (name, value) satisfies the boolean expression. After all leafs of AndNode or OrNode are evaluated, AND and OR operations are executed. Evaluation is done using a visitor.
    Author:
    razvan
